## ğŸš€ Quick Start (DVP-PRO)

### InstalaciÃ³n
```bash
git clone https://github.com/tu-usuario/fraud_detection.git
cd fraud_detection
pip install -r requirements.txt
pip install -e .
```

### EjecuciÃ³n
1) **Pipeline ML (CLI)**
```bash
fraud-train --train-path data/processed/train_clean.parquet/part.0.parquet \
            --val-path data/processed/validation_clean.parquet
fraud-evaluate --test-path data/processed/test_clean.parquet
fraud-predict --input-path data/processed/test_clean.parquet \
              --output-path reports/predictions/predicciones.csv
```

2) **API REST (con auth)**
```bash
fraud-api
# o
uvicorn api.main:app --reload
```
Endpoints principales:
- `POST /api/v1/predict` â€” predicciÃ³n individual
- `POST /api/v1/predict/batch` â€” batch (â‰¤1000)
- `GET /api/v1/model/info` â€” info del modelo
- `PUT /api/v1/model/threshold?new_threshold=0.6` â€” actualizar threshold  
Docs: http://localhost:8000/docs

Auth rÃ¡pida (token JWT simplificado):
```bash
curl -X POST "http://localhost:8000/token" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded" \
  -d "username=admin&password=admin123"
```

3) **Dashboard (Streamlit)**
```bash
